narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class complicates simple topics. Take a harder class and learn more.
Take it if you must (i.e. it's a prerequisite) but maybe seek out another class if you are looking for a QR credit.
It depends. The class is challenging, but you do learn a lot.

If you can learn from the book, take this class. If not, better find a tutor. Instructors are terrible but if you look at past exams and understand the answers, you can do well. Recommend if you have a good background knowledge in math
